  "texts": [
    "Thus, a key consideration in suspense generation is reasoning about what characters know versus what readers know.",
    "O 'Neill and Riedl (2014) attempt to create a computational model of the accounting of suspense (Gerrig and Bernardo, 1994).",
    "In order to determine whether a story might be perceived as suspenseful, they generate plans for the protagonist and analyze the quantity and quality of possible plans.",
    "However, since they use a symbolic planner, they must know the characters and possible actions in advance, limiting practical applicability.",
    "Their detection technique does not lend itself to story generation."
